Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Recognize veridian as a valid OS in GCC's config.sub

GCC ships its own copy of config.sub (at the top level of the source
tree).  This patch mirrors the change made to binutils' config.sub so
that GCC's configure scripts can parse x86_64-veridian,
aarch64-veridian, and riscv64-veridian target triples.

The entry is added right after the long list of recognized OS names
(ending with -mon960*, -lnews*) and before the -mac* rewrite rule.
---
 config.sub | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/config.sub b/config.sub
index 38f3d037a78..c91e5327b01 100755
--- a/config.sub
+++ b/config.sub
@@ -1743,6 +1743,9 @@ case $os in
 	     | -sim | -xray | -os68k* | -none | -v88r* \
 	     | -windows* | -osx | -abug | -netware* | -os9* \
 	     | -macos* | -mpw* | -magic* | -mmixware* | -mon960* | -lnews*)
+		;;
+	-veridian*)
+		# VeridianOS -- capability-based microkernel
 		;;
 	-mac*)
 		os=`echo "$os" | sed -e 's|mac|macos|'`
